<bibRefCitation id="EFD34B4CFFD7FFCBFE9A778135EBFE02" author="Koste, W." box="[357,500,404,428]" pageId="9" pagination="258 - 505" refId="ref4713" refString="Koste, W. (1972) Rotatorien aus Gewassern Amazoniens. Amazoniana, 3 (3 / 4), 258 - 505." type="journal article" year="1972">Koste, 1972</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD34B4CFFD7FFCBFDFA7781377BFE02" author="Koste, W. &amp; Jose de Paggi, S." box="[517,868,404,429]" pageId="9" pagination="71 - 102" refId="ref4738" refString="Koste, W. &amp; Jose de Paggi, S. (1982) Rotifera of the superorder Monogononta recorded from Neotropis. Gewasser und Abwasser, 68 / 69, 71 - 102." type="journal article" year="1982">Koste &amp; Jose de Paggi, 1982</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD34B4CFFD7FFCBFC8A77803073FE02" author="Vasquez, E. &amp; Pardo, M. J. &amp; Zoppi de Roa, E. &amp; Lopez, C." box="[885,1132,404,429]" pageId="9" pagination="11 - 24" refId="ref5711" refString="Vasquez, E., Pardo, M. J., Zoppi de Roa, E. &amp; Lopez, C. (1998) Rotifer fauna from Venezuela. Amazoniana, 15 (1 / 2), 11 - 24." type="journal article" year="1998">
Vásquez 
<emphasis id="B936EAAFFFD7FFCBFC1E77813007FE03" box="[993,1048,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="9">et al</emphasis>
., 1998
</bibRefCitation>
; Garcia-Morales &amp; Elias- Gutierrez, 2004; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD34B4CFFD7FFCBFEA577A336B0FE7E" author="Garraffoni, A. R. S. &amp; Lourenco, A. P." box="[346,687,439,464]" pageId="9" pagination="375 - 407" refId="ref4437" refString="Garraffoni, A. R. S. &amp; Lourenco, A. P. (2012) Synthesis of Brazilian Rotifera: An updated list of species. Check List, 8 (3), 375 - 407. https: // doi. org / 10.15560 / 8.3.375" type="journal article" year="2012">Garraffoni &amp; Lourenço, 2012</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD34B4CFFD7FFCBFD4377A337CAFE7E" author="Ferrando, N. S. &amp; Claps, M. C." box="[700,981,439,464]" pageId="9" pagination="1 - 25" refId="ref4183" refString="Ferrando, N. S. &amp; Claps, M. C. (2016) A revised and updated checklist of Monogononta rotifers from Argentina. Check List, 12 (4), 1 - 25. https: // doi. org / 10.15560 / 12.4.1942" type="journal article" year="2016">Ferrando &amp; Claps, 2016</bibRefCitation>
), Palaearctic? (
<bibRefCitation id="EFD34B4CFFD7FFCBFB7D77A33134FE7E" author="Sudzuki, M." box="[1154,1323,439,464]" pageId="9" pagination="29 - 70" refId="ref5554" refString="Sudzuki, M. (1992) Seasonal and local occurrences of the Rotifera in southwestern islands of Japan. Japanese Society of Systematic Zoology, 46, 29 - 70, pls. 1 - 32." type="journal article" year="1992">Sudzuki, 1992</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD34B4CFFD7FFCBFAC677A334E3FE5B" author="Salem, T. &amp; Karima, M. Y. &amp; Bedir, S. &amp; Yousry, M." pageId="9" pagination="29 - 40" refId="ref5344" refString="Salem, T., Karima, M. Y., Bedir, S. &amp; Yousry, M. (2016) Ecological aspects with new zooplankter record at Lake Nasser, Egypt. Life Science Journal, 13 (9), 29 - 40." type="journal article" year="2016">
Salem 
<emphasis id="B936EAAFFFD7FFCBFA7777AD34B2FE5B" italics="true" pageId="9">et al</emphasis>
., 2016
</bibRefCitation>
) and Oriental (
<bibRefCitation id="EFD34B4CFFD7FFCBFE5877C8367CFE5A" author="Umi, W. A. D. &amp; Yusoff, F. M. &amp; Aris, A. Z. &amp; Sharip, Z." box="[423,611,476,501]" pageId="9" pagination="795 - 807" refId="ref5636" refString="Umi, W. A. D., Yusoff, F. M., Aris, A. Z. &amp; Sharip, Z. (2018) Rotifer community structure in tropical lakes with different environmental characteristics related to ecosystem health. Journal of Environmental Biology, 39, 795 - 807. https: // doi. org / 10.22438 / jeb / 39 / 5 (si) / 30" type="journal article" year="2018">
Umi 
<emphasis id="B936EAAFFFD7FFCBFE1D77C9360DFE5B" box="[482,530,476,501]" italics="true" pageId="9">et al</emphasis>
., 2018
</bibRefCitation>
) regions, with most records from the Nearctic and Neotropis. Ours is the first record for 
<collectingCountry id="F355762DFFD7FFCBFEBE77EB3597FDB6" box="[321,392,511,536]" name="China" pageId="9">China</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3586536FFD7FFCBFF2F74313659FCBA" pageId="9" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="8BFD36BDFFD7FFCBFF2F74313659FCBA" blockId="9.[151,1437,151,789]" pageId="9">
<taxonomicName id="4C424D3EFFD7FFCBFF2F74313568FD93" authorityName="Myers" authorityYear="1934" box="[208,375,548,573]" class="Eurotatoria" family="Flosculariidae" genus="Ptygura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Flosculariaceae" pageId="9" phylum="Rotifera" rank="species" species="libera">
<emphasis id="B936EAAFFFD7FFCBFF2F74313568FD93" box="[208,375,548,573]" italics="true" pageId="9">Ptygura libera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known as a warm-stenotherm (
<bibRefCitation id="EFD34B4CFFD7FFCBFCFD743037B0FD93" author="Nogrady, T." box="[770,943,548,573]" pageId="9" pagination="425 - 436" refId="ref5249" refString="Nogrady, T. (1976) Canadian rotifers. I. Lac Echo, Quebec. Le Naturaliste Canadien, 103, 425 - 436." type="journal article" year="1976">Nogrady, 1976</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD34B4CFFD7FFCBFC41743130A1FD92" author="Koste, W. &amp; Tobias, W." box="[958,1214,548,573]" pageId="9" pagination="499 - 515" refId="ref4773" refString="Koste, W. &amp; Tobias, W. (1987) Zur Radertierfauna des Sankarani-Stausees im Einzugsgebiet des Niger, Republik Mali, Westafrika (Aschelminthes: Rotatoria). Archiv fur Hydrobiologie, 108, 499 - 515." type="journal article" year="1987">Koste &amp; Tobias, 1987</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD34B4CFFD7FFCBFB3274303593FDCE" author="Garcia-Morales, A. E. &amp; Elias-Gutierrez, M." pageId="9" pagination="99 - 120" refId="ref4387" refString="Garcia-Morales, A. E. &amp; Elias-Gutierrez, M. (2004) Rotifera from southeastern Mexico, new records and comments on zoogeography. Anales del Institute de Biologia, Universidad Nacional Autonoma de Mexico, Serie Zoologia, 75 (1), 99 - 120." type="journal article" year="2004">Garcia-Morales &amp; Elias-Gutierrez, 2004</bibRefCitation>
), that prefers less nutrient rich waters (
<bibRefCitation id="EFD34B4CFFD7FFCBFCC374533014FDCE" author="Salem, T. &amp; Karima, M. Y. &amp; Bedir, S. &amp; Yousry, M." box="[828,1035,583,608]" pageId="9" pagination="29 - 40" refId="ref5344" refString="Salem, T., Karima, M. Y., Bedir, S. &amp; Yousry, M. (2016) Ecological aspects with new zooplankter record at Lake Nasser, Egypt. Life Science Journal, 13 (9), 29 - 40." type="journal article" year="2016">
Salem 
<emphasis id="B936EAAFFFD7FFCBFC74745D37A3FDCE" box="[907,956,583,608]" italics="true" pageId="9">et al</emphasis>
., 2016
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD34B4CFFD7FFCBFBE8745330D0FDCE" author="Umi, W. A. D. &amp; Yusoff, F. M. &amp; Aris, A. Z. &amp; Sharip, Z." box="[1047,1231,583,608]" pageId="9" pagination="795 - 807" refId="ref5636" refString="Umi, W. A. D., Yusoff, F. M., Aris, A. Z. &amp; Sharip, Z. (2018) Rotifer community structure in tropical lakes with different environmental characteristics related to ecosystem health. Journal of Environmental Biology, 39, 795 - 807. https: // doi. org / 10.22438 / jeb / 39 / 5 (si) / 30" type="journal article" year="2018">
Umi 
<emphasis id="B936EAAFFFD7FFCBFBB0745D309FFDCE" box="[1103,1152,583,608]" italics="true" pageId="9">et al</emphasis>
., 2018
</bibRefCitation>
) and tolerates low pH (
<bibRefCitation id="EFD34B4CFFD7FFCBFF3574783548FD2A" author="Koste, W." box="[202,343,620,644]" pageId="9" pagination="258 - 505" refId="ref4713" refString="Koste, W. (1972) Rotatorien aus Gewassern Amazoniens. Amazoniana, 3 (3 / 4), 258 - 505." type="journal article" year="1972">Koste, 1972</bibRefCitation>
; 1978; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD34B4CFFD7FFCBFE5274783671FD2A" author="Umi, W. A. D. &amp; Yusoff, F. M. &amp; Aris, A. Z. &amp; Sharip, Z." box="[429,622,620,645]" pageId="9" pagination="795 - 807" refId="ref5636" refString="Umi, W. A. D., Yusoff, F. M., Aris, A. Z. &amp; Sharip, Z. (2018) Rotifer community structure in tropical lakes with different environmental characteristics related to ecosystem health. Journal of Environmental Biology, 39, 795 - 807. https: // doi. org / 10.22438 / jeb / 39 / 5 (si) / 30" type="journal article" year="2018">
Umi 
<emphasis id="B936EAAFFFD7FFCBFE1774793605FD2B" box="[488,538,620,645]" italics="true" pageId="9">et al</emphasis>
., 2018
</bibRefCitation>
). It frequently occurs as a dominant species in lakes and reservoirs 
<emphasis id="B936EAAFFFD7FFCBFA8B7479318AFD2A" box="[1396,1429,621,644]" italics="true" pageId="9">etc</emphasis>
. (
<emphasis id="B936EAAFFFD7FFCBFF5F748534D7FD06" box="[160,200,657,680]" italics="true" pageId="9">e.g.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFD34B4CFFD7FFCBFF2F749B3566FD06" author="Nogrady, T." box="[208,377,655,680]" pageId="9" pagination="425 - 436" refId="ref5249" refString="Nogrady, T. (1976) Canadian rotifers. I. Lac Echo, Quebec. Le Naturaliste Canadien, 103, 425 - 436." type="journal article" year="1976">Nogrady, 1976</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD34B4CFFD7FFCBFE7B74843662FD06" author="Koste, W. &amp; Tobias, W." box="[388,637,655,680]" pageId="9" pagination="499 - 515" refId="ref4773" refString="Koste, W. &amp; Tobias, W. (1987) Zur Radertierfauna des Sankarani-Stausees im Einzugsgebiet des Niger, Republik Mali, Westafrika (Aschelminthes: Rotatoria). Archiv fur Hydrobiologie, 108, 499 - 515." type="journal article" year="1987">Koste &amp; Tobias, 1987</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD34B4CFFD7FFCBFD76749B3727FD06" author="Siegfried, C. A." box="[649,824,655,680]" pageId="9" pagination="441 - 462" refId="ref5486" refString="Siegfried, C. A. (1991) The pelagic rotifer community of an acidic clearwater lake in the Adirondack Mountains of New York State. Archiv fur Hydrobiologie, 122, 441 - 462." type="journal article" year="1991">Siegfried, 1991</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD34B4CFFD7FFCBFCBB749B3013FD06" author="Stemberger, R. S." box="[836,1036,655,680]" pageId="9" pagination="283 - 302" refId="ref5523" refString="Stemberger, R. S. (1990) An inventory of rotifer species diversity of northern Michigan inland lakes. Archiv fur Hydrobiologie, 118, 283 - 302." type="journal article" year="1990">Stemberger, 1990</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD34B4CFFD7FFCBFBE7749B30CBFD06" author="Umi, W. A. D. &amp; Yusoff, F. M. &amp; Aris, A. Z. &amp; Sharip, Z." box="[1048,1236,655,680]" pageId="9" pagination="795 - 807" refId="ref5636" refString="Umi, W. A. D., Yusoff, F. M., Aris, A. Z. &amp; Sharip, Z. (2018) Rotifer community structure in tropical lakes with different environmental characteristics related to ecosystem health. Journal of Environmental Biology, 39, 795 - 807. https: // doi. org / 10.22438 / jeb / 39 / 5 (si) / 30" type="journal article" year="2018">
Umi 
<emphasis id="B936EAAFFFD7FFCBFBAE7485309DFD06" box="[1105,1154,655,680]" italics="true" pageId="9">et al</emphasis>
., 2018
</bibRefCitation>
). The species was found in summer, when it dominated the rotifer community of the Huguangyan Lake, an oligo-/mesotrophic closed maar lake with relatively low nutrient and chlorophyll content (
<bibRefCitation id="EFD34B4CFFD7FFCBFC9B74C33027FD5E" author="Zhang, G. W. &amp; Huang, X. H. &amp; Li, C. L. &amp; Zeng, Y. Y." box="[868,1080,727,752]" pageId="9" pagination="70 - 75" refId="ref6274" refString="Zhang, G. W., Huang, X. H., Li, C. L. &amp; Zeng, Y. Y. (2015) Correlation analysis between Chlorophyll a and water quality indices in Huguangyan maar lake and its eutrophication evaluation. Journal of Guangdong Ocean University, 35 (1), 70 - 75. [in Chinese]" type="journal article" year="2015">
Zhang 
<emphasis id="B936EAAFFFD7FFCBFC4A74CD37F9FD5E" box="[949,998,727,752]" italics="true" pageId="9">et al</emphasis>
., 2015
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD34B4CFFD7FFCBFBBA74C33114FD5E" author="Chen, F. J. &amp; Lao, Q. B. &amp; Bian, P. W. &amp; Zhu, Q. M. &amp; Zhou, F. X. &amp; Zhou, X. &amp; Meng, Y. F. &amp; Wang, M. Y." box="[1093,1291,727,752]" pageId="9" pagination="1693 - 1706" refId="ref3844" refString="Chen, F. J., Lao, Q. B., Bian, P. W., Zhu, Q. M., Zhou, F. X., Zhou, X., Meng, Y. F. &amp; Wang, M. Y. (2018) Spatial and temporal distributions of nutrients and their influencing factors in the Huguangyan Maar Lake. Journal of Lake Sciences, 30 (6), 1693 - 1706. [in Chinese] https: // doi. org / 10.18307 / 2018.0621" type="journal article" year="2018">
Chen 
<emphasis id="B936EAAFFFD7FFCBFB7774CD30A5FD5E" box="[1160,1210,727,752]" italics="true" pageId="9">et al</emphasis>
., 2018
</bibRefCitation>
), confirming the ecological preferences of 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D3EFFD7FFCBFE1F74E93620FCBB" authorityName="Myers" authorityYear="1934" box="[480,575,764,789]" class="Eurotatoria" family="Flosculariidae" genus="Ptygura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Flosculariaceae" pageId="9" phylum="Rotifera" rank="species" species="libera">
<emphasis id="B936EAAFFFD7FFCBFE1F74E93620FCBB" box="[480,575,764,789]" italics="true" pageId="9">P. libera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
